importance

Interface ImportanceIF<E>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ExternalImportanceIF<E>, InternalImportanceIF
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Average, AverageSplitIndex, ChisqOnTwoConfusionTables, KSTestOnTreePredPerfs, PermImportance, VariableCount

    public interface ImportanceIF<E>
    This defines a global interface for classes that compute feature importance. E is the type of the computed variable importance measure. For instance, if we wish to compute an array containing the average gini value of each variable, E could be double[].
